body.text:
People stuck with lower view counts on their IG Reels are usually making the same mistake: wrong audience, wrong message.

Here’s the fix I recommend to every client who wants to grow faster: the 3x3 hashtag strategy. 

- Use 1–3 hashtags about your ideal audience
- Use 1–3 about the solution you deliver
- Use 1–3 about the struggles your audience is actively facing

How to find the right hashtags:

Step 1: Search keywords your audience would use (not what you call yourself, but what they call themselves) and save the ones with 10K–500K posts.

Step 2: Look at hashtags your competitors or niche accounts are using and borrow the ones that are getting them engagement.

Step 3: Use Instagram’s “related hashtags” feature: type your keyword in the search bar, scroll down, and pull 2–3 ideas from the suggestions list.

This method forces your content into the right conversations. It’s the difference between being ignored and being in demand.

#ContentCreators #InstagramGrowthTips #LowEngagement

� A behind-the-scenes look at how AI agents are being applied in manual testing

body.text:
The world changed in November 2022, and honestly,  we’re never going back.

When ChatGPT 3.5 launched, it wasn’t just a cool new tool.

It pulled us into a brand new era of AI-driven marketing.

And if you’re a Google Ads marketer, you probably felt one of two things:

Excitement or apprehension.

Since then, only a small percentage of marketers have successfully integrated AI into their daily workflow. Even fewer are tapping into the full power of deep learning tools that are rapidly evolving right before our eyes.

Here’s what I believe:

AI is the single greatest opportunity digital marketers have ever had.

From large language models like ChatGPT to image generators and advanced data processors, these tools are transforming how we build, launch, and optimize campaigns.

They’re giving solopreneurs, small businesses, and even massive enterprise teams the power to operate like a full-stack marketing agency.

According to reports, only 30% of marketers say they’ve fully adopted AI into their operations.

CEOs everywhere are declaring that the employees who embrace AI are quickly becoming the most valuable in their organizations.

It’s no longer a luxury. It’s a competitive edge.

As for me?

I couldn’t imagine running Google Ads the same way we did pre-2022.

I’ve built an AI-driven workflow with custom prompts, templates, and strategies that make my process 100x more efficient and more fun.

So if you’ve been struggling to keep up or are unsure where to start with AI, you’re in luck.

I am opening up my new program “The 7-day AI Workflow for Google AdWords” to new students with a limited time special. You can claim that special, and get a free prompt, by clicking below.
